text: Tayla McAuliffe (born 15 March 1999) is an Australian rules footballer who played for the Fremantle Football Club in the AFL Women's (AFLW). After being overlooked in the national draft days earlier, McAuliffe was eventually drafted by Fremantle with their fourth selection and 19th and final pick overall in the 2017 AFL Women's rookie draft. She made her debut in an 18-point loss to at Fremantle Oval in round 5 of the 2018 season. == References == == External links == * Category:1999 births Category:Living people Category:Fremantle Football Club (AFLW) players Category:Australian rules footballers from Western Australia
